Armed struggle: the MP3 player against the mobile.
We advise you how to choose
While almost all mobile plays MP3 files, no MP3 player can make calls.
It seems clear that it is better to buy only the phone.
Yet there are enough reasons for man to acquire only the player.
The choice practically depends on the way it is used and the requirement of the future owner.
It will probably be difficult for him to acquire the most modern record to listen to Maxim Turbulenc's latest album on it.
On the other hand, this type of music products such as LP discs no longer come out, and in terms of their quality there is not a single objective reason to continue buying them.
If vinyl records with art rock, jazz, or blues music are tucked into your shelves, you’re probably dreaming, at least, of this type of record.
This is the same with the music that is on the way, that is, the compressed, simplified music - the music in MP3.
And here there are price and quality categories.
For some it may be unacceptable to spend 8,000 crowns on a player, as well as for a Pink Floyd lover who will hardly test the twenty-crown merchant helmets.
Two ends, between which there is enough space for each.
The choice is wide.
It also determines the battery life
Some of the best players get a lot more than just playing music and even what not even most mobiles.
No current device is as universal as the phone.
Faced with the most basic features like calling, messaging, you can play music and video, record both, have a better or worse camera and even get to navigate.
And when we take into account the Smartphone and the PDAs will have in their pocket also a small computer.
This is a small miracle as no refrigerator knows how to make a grill and no television can photograph.
The universality of mobile also brings us disadvantages.
The more features you use on your phone, the sooner the screen indicator will be lit asking to be recharged.
And the reproduction of music is one of the biggest energy tragons.
Few are the mobiles that can play music for more than ten or twelve hours, most much less.
In this sense, music players (especially the simplest ones) clearly have a higher performance.
Therefore, keep in mind that cheap phones will not play for more than two hours.
If in addition to this, above, they constantly call for still, for more safety, a charger for work - this is also true for the more expensive appliances.
With the MP3 player this problem is not going to have, as even the worst ones last at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation after a load.
Another problem happens when you record music on your mobile.
Unfortunately only a part of the devices has the universal USB connector and, moreover, not all of them can connect directly to the computer without special software.
Of course it is possible to record music directly on the memory card but only in some non-reduction reader units can connect the small memory cards that are used on the mobiles.
In the players, with some exception (iPod), no special software is required.
Simply fill the device with music via the computer's USB.
